               <titlePart>
                  <title>
                     <lb/>
                     <lb/>P O E M S <lb/>
                     <lb/>
                     <hi rend="small">on the <lb/>
                        <lb/>
                        <emph>NAMING OF
                                                  PLACES.</emph>
                     </hi>
                  </title>
               </titlePart>
            </docTitle>
         </titlePage>
         <pb n="176"/>
         <argument xml:id="ARGUnp">
            <pb n="177"/>
            <head>ADVERTISEMENT. </head>
            <p>By Persons resident in the country and attached to rural objects,
                                   many places will be found unnamed or of unknown names, where
                                   little Incidents will have occurred, or feelings been
                                   experienced, which will have given to such places a private and
                                   peculiar interest. From a wish to give some sort of record to
                                   such Incidents or renew the gratification of such Feelings, Names
                                   have been given to Places by the Author and some of his Friends,
                                   and the following Poems written in consequence. </p>
         </argument>
         <pb n="178"/>
      </front>
